---
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
---

<MarketingLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Elite Project"
  description="Learn how Elite Project collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-slate-950 text-slate-100">
    <div
      class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(circle_at_top,_rgba(67,56,202,0.18),_transparent_60%)]"
    >
    </div>
    <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 pb-24 pt-28">
      <p
        class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.35em] text-slate-400"
      >
        Legal
      </p>
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-semibold text-white sm:text-5xl">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-base text-slate-300">
        Last updated: October 23, 2025
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-slate-950/80 py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl space-y-12 px-6 text-slate-300">
      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
          Information We Collect
        </h2>
        <p>
          Elite Project is a static site template designed for GitHub Pages
          deployment. As a static site, we do not collect, store, or process any
          personal data directly.
        </p>
        <p>
          When you contact us via email (through the contact form or directly),
          your email provider and our email service will handle your
          communication according to their respective privacy policies.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          If you deploy this template and integrate third-party services
          (analytics, form processors, etc.), those services may collect data
          according to their own privacy policies. We recommend reviewing the
          privacy policies of any services you integrate.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">GitHub Pages</h2>
        <p>
          This site is hosted on GitHub Pages. GitHub may collect visitor IP
          addresses and other technical information for security and compliance
          purposes. Please review GitHub's privacy statement for more
          information.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p>
          The base Elite Project template does not use cookies or tracking
          scripts. The theme preference you select is stored locally in your
          browser's localStorage and never transmitted to any server.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          As a static site with no backend, there is no database or server-side
          processing of user data. All content is delivered as pre-built HTML,
          CSS, and JavaScript files.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Since we do not collect or store personal data, there is no data to
          access, modify, or delete. If you have questions about data collected
          by third-party services you've integrated, please contact those
          services directly.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
          Changes to This Policy
        </h2>
        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. Changes will be
          posted on this page with an updated revision date.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at
          <a
            href="mailto:hello@eliteproject.dev"
            class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300"
          >
            hello@eliteproject.dev
          </a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</MarketingLayout>
